On January 20, 2009, Barack Obama, the President of the United States, proclaimed it to be a National Day of Renewal and Reconciliation. In his proclamation, he acknowledged the challenges and uncertainties faced by the nation but emphasized the resilience and strength of the American people. He called for unity and urged citizens to come together to carry forward the legacy of American democracy. The proclamation referenced a quote from President Abraham Lincoln, highlighting the importance of remembering the sacrifices made for the country and the need to tap into the better nature of individuals. Obama called upon all citizens to serve one another and work towards remaking the nation for the new century.